<p><span>■Consultation Services for Visitors to Osaka from Abroad.<span>【Telephone Consultation Services and Inquiry Counters】</span><span> ・ We at the Osaka Convention and Tourism Bureau have opened the following telephone consultation services and inquiry counters.</span><span><a href="http://ofw-oer.com/call/en/">Osaka Call Center </a> Tourist Information Centres </span></span><span>(<a href="https://osaka-info.jp/en/page/tourist-information-shin-osaka">Shin-Osaka </a> , <a href="https://osaka-info.jp/en/page/tourist-information-osaka">Osaka </a>,<a href="https://osaka-info.jp/en/page/tourist-information-namba"> Namba </a>).</span></p>
<p><span><span>・The Japan National Tourism Association (JNTO) operates a
 24-hour Japan Visitor Hotline. This multilingual hotline can be used 
for accident and emergency situations as well as for general tourist 
information. If you require emergency support or advice, please contact 
the following number. <a href="https://www.japan.travel/en/plan/hotline/">Japan Visitor Hotline </a> Tel 050-3816-2787</span></span></p>
<p><span><span>【Online Information Regarding Medical Facilities】 For 
additional information regarding medical facilities with multilingual 
support: ・Osaka Prefectural Government Homepage “Osaka Medical Net for 
Foreigners”: <a href="https://www.mfis.pref.osaka.jp/omfo/">https://www.mfis.pref.osaka.jp/omfo/ </a> ・<a href="https://www.osakasafetravels.com/en/">Osaka Safe Travels </a>
 To ensure the safety of overseas travelers, provides disaster-related 
information such as emergency shelters and transportation. Must-visit 
website while traveling in Osaka. ・The Japan National Tourism 
Association Homepage <a href="https://www.jnto.go.jp/emergency/eng/mi_guide.html">https://www.jnto.go.jp/emergency/eng/mi_guide.html </a></span></span></p>
<p><span>We wish a safe and enjoyable stay to all of those visiting Osaka at this present time.</span></p>
<p><span>Telephone numbers in case of emergency</span></p>
<p>This is a list of contact information which you need to know in case 
of emergency such as accidents, natural disasters or injuries, etc. for 
notification and information gathering.It is effective that you confirm 
the contact information in advance so as to stay calm and act properly 
in case of emergency.</p>
<p>Crime/ Accident</p>
<p>Please call the emergency number of the police " 110".</p>
<p><a href="https://www.police.pref.osaka.lg.jp/foreign_languag_selection/english/3/1/1/3954.html" rel="noreferrer noopener">How to call Dial 110</a> (Website of the Osaka Prefectural Police Department）</p>
<p>【Reference】</p>
<p><a href="https://www.police.pref.osaka.lg.jp/foreign_languag_selection/english/2/index.html" rel="noreferrer noopener">The Police Box ("Koban") at Minami and Kita area</a> （Website of the Osaka Prefectural Police Department）</p>
<p><a href="https://www.police.pref.osaka.lg.jp/foreign_languag_selection/english/3/2/3958.html" rel="noreferrer noopener">Information about police stations in Osaka city</a> （Website of the Osaka Prefectural Police Department）</p>
<p><a href="https://www.police.pref.osaka.lg.jp/foreign_languag_selection/english/3/2/3957.html" rel="noreferrer noopener">Information about police stations outside Osaka city</a> （Website of the Osaka Prefectural Police Department）</p>
<p>Fire / Ambulance</p>
<p>Please call the emergency number of the fire department " 119".</p>
<p><a href="http://www.city.osaka.lg.jp/contents/wdu020/shobo/english/e03/if_02.html" rel="noreferrer noopener">How to call Dial 119</a> （Website of the Osaka Municipal Fire Department）</p>
<h3>Disasters</h3>
<p><a href="http://www.jnto.go.jp/safety-tips/pc/index.html" rel="noreferrer noopener">Safety tips for travelers</a> (Website of the Japan Tourism Agency)</p>
<p>The purpose of this website is to provide information to ensure safe travel for foreign tourists visiting Japan.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.jnto.go.jp/eng/arrange/essential/emergency/safety_tips.html" rel="noreferrer noopener">Application"Safety tips"</a> (Website of JNTO)</p>
<p>"Safety tips" is a push-enabled app for Earthquake Early Warning and Tsunami Warning within Japan</p>
<p><a href="http://www.osaka-bousai.net.e.add.hp.transer.com/pref/index.html" rel="noreferrer noopener">Osaka disaster prevention net</a> （Website of Osaka Prefecture）</p>
<p><a href="http://www.mlit.go.jp/river/bousai/olympic/en/index.html" rel="noreferrer noopener">Disaster Prevention Portal</a><span> (Website of the Ministry of Land, Infrastructure, Transport and Tourism)</span><span>This
 portal site provides information related to disasters that may occur in
 Tokyo as well as useful disaster prevention information. This is a 
precautionary measure taken in case the Tokyo metropolitan area is 
directly affected by harmful seismic activity. In particular, it has 
been set up in preparation for the 2020 Olympic and Paralympic games in 
Tokyo. </span></p>
